design in what I&#39;ve always heard was sunken relief...if that makes sense.

Since you are involved with the NTHK, let me ask this. The name Namban 
(Nanban, in modern terms, so I hear) is a general term. There are the 
sub-catagories for those fittings. However, I&#39;ve noticed that the NBTHK, 
auction houses, dealers, etc. (I don&#39;t have any NTHK examples) do not get so 
specific and call these things, &quot;Namban.&quot; (Except perhaps for the most 
earliest examples?) Care to comment on this thinking for all to see??? 
